                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; a few lines on the incipit page of the
                           text, alternating with black lines; incipit of each section of the text;
                           abbreviations; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic
                           numerals; some other words, e.g., halle luya (e.g., fols. 6ra, 7rb),
                           wa-kaʾǝbä (e.g., fols. 11ra, 12vb), ṣällǝyu (e.g., fols. 11ra, 13ra),
                           ʾǝgäle (e.g., fols. 14ra, 15ra), qǝdmä (e.g., fols. 49vb, 50va), wa-ʾǝmzǝ
                           (e.g., fols. 53va, 54vb).</seg>
                     </handNote>
